About this Document
Purpose
The document gives a brief description of the API specification, the accepted parameters and the expected request/ response.


Intended Audience
SBI Application teams 
APIs interaction with EDMS

APIs interacting with EDMS should be encrypted and decrypted at both the ends with source authentication and RSA algorithm.  The request to the API is expected to be in JSON format. An encrypted response is advisable.
Business acceptance scenario
•	e-DMS API service integration with <Respective application> front end to update the uploaded documents.
•	EDMS team will define and whitelist the application ID (according to different source applications and channels) at EDMS end.
•	Re-upload & Update document will create a new version and always-new version will be retrieved on enquiry. 
•	All the communication between source and destination will be done in encrypted format using source authentication logic and RSA algorithm. 
•	Approach for Source Authentication (encryption/decryption logic) will not work with anything less than Java 8 version. 
•	Metadata sanitization of uploaded file (Base64 content) will be done at EDMS end.
•	Exif metadata from images will be removed and same is stored at EDMS end (Exif removed Base64 content). Also during search Exif removed base64 will be shown.
•	As per ISD recommendations, EDMS is not allowing below special characters in document name for uploading-
 !#$%&~'*+,/:;<=>?@^`|


1.	Update document of EDMS
Purpose:
The purpose of the API is to update existing document, which can be done by uploading the document with the same parameters that were entered during initial upload. The documents update can be based on Document ID and Unique identifier / reference number. A latest version will be created and stored in eDMS. 

“SBI application Name (ApplicationID) -> Unique identifier -> Documents”



Assumption:
•	To update the documents, applicationID and branch code is mandatory field. 
•	Base64 string for all the documents should be provided in request.
•	To update existing document, request string will consist of Branch code, Application ID,  Unique identifier / reference number which were entered during initial document upload along with Document ID generated by eDMS for that document.

